Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharpish turn. Stamped on turn. Circular stamp with rose symbol; re-cut. Clay fine buff.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name, Menon. Athens, Agora SS1646 is similarly re-cut and is of the same month, but not the same original die, and it has the genitive of the month name, not the nominative. SS4097, also Menon, is re-cut with month Sminthios. Name Menon.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0657)
